dismissalText.commentary: Neil Broom run out (Ponting) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: run out, Guptill's running out of partners here, full on the off stump, defended towards point and they attempt a quick single, Ponting runs in, picks the ball cleanly and throws down the stumps at the striker's end in one motion to find Broom well short of his ground. Could that be the decisive blow?

commentTextItems.html: slapped in front of square, towards deep cover

commentPostTextItems.html: It has started raining pretty heavily in Brisbane now. Bucknor shakes his head, has an elaborate consultation with his partner. Under normal circumstances, the players would have gone off.

Bucknor has a word with Ponting, and the batsmen, and they all walk off. This is disappointing. We've had a superb game and it's really unfortunate to see it end in this manner. The captains are shaking hands in the pavilion, and New Zealand will feel unlucky. Diamanti and Guptill had added 50 for the seventh wicket, and with 33 needed off 6 overs with four wickets in hand, the batting side held a slight edge.

It's pouring in Brisbane now and its highly unlikely we'll have any more play. The match is officially called off, Australia retain the Chappell-Hadlee trophy as a result of having won it on the previous occasion.

Just as a note of clarification, Duckworth-Lewis does not come into the picture here. Both sides need to have batted at least 20 overs for that rule to apply. New Zealand just batted 14 overs, so the match is inconclusive.

That's all we have from here folks. It's a tragedy the series had to end this way. It was fun bringing you the ODI series, and do tune in to the Twenty20 match between the two teams on February 15. Just for your information, no Man of the Match has been announced for this game, but Michael Hussey has been handed the Man-of-the-Series award. Thanks for all your feedback. Adios!

commentTextItems.html: short of a length outside off, plays and misses

commentPreTextItems.html: A good crowd of 20,581 at the Gabba today

commentTextItems.html: pushed to David Hussey at cover and they take a quick single, a direct hit would have been close
full on the pads, flicked away through square leg, fine leg takes some time to reach the ball and the batsmen are back for the second
short of a length outside off, tries to cut that over point, is into the shot too early, misses

commentPreTextItems.html: 38 needed off 7 overs. Hilfenhaus comes in to bowl

commentTextItems.html: firmly struck, full outside off, drilled down the ground for a single
lands on a good length on the off stump, plays across the line, gets a thick edge over point for a couple towards third man

headshotImage.caption: James Hopes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Hopes player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: short on the off stump and swung away, tried to defend off the back foot, beat the outside edge
full on middle and off, tries to drive it down the ground to long-on, gets a thick outside edge towards third man
short of a good length outside off, opens the face to play it wide of point for a single
played and missed, short of a good length outside off, prodded at it, failed to connect

commentPreTextItems.html: 42 needed of eight overs here. New Zealand are well ahead on the run-rate

commentTextItems.html: good length outside off, slashes hard at it, misses
superb shot! Good length on middle and leg, too straight, he turns it away behind square, well wide of short fine leg for a boundary. The visitors are fighting back well here

headshotImage.caption: James Hopes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Hopes player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full and a touch too wide, the batsman reaches for it, misses
he's looking good here, short of a good length outside off, chopped down over point for three runs, Siddle dives at deep point to drag the ball just back in
short on middle and leg, pulled away powerfully wide of midwicket for a boundary, good confident short from Diamanti
shot! Full outside off, driven uppishly towards deep extra cover for a couple
full outside off, driven firmly on the bounce wide of the bowler for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: New Zealand still have their two powerplay overs intact

commentTextItems.html: short of a good length on middle and leg, tries to whip it away off his hips, gets an inside edge onto his pads
bowled full on the leg stump from wide of the crease, tried to glace it fine, hit on the pads and they get a leg bye

dismissalText.commentary: Peter Fulton c Ferguson b Bracken 22 (12b 2x4 2x6 14m) SR: 183.33

dismissalComment.html: gone! Fulton's thrown away his wicket! Short of a length on the off stump, he makes room to cut that over point, gets the top-edge and Ferguson runs a few steps back to pouch an good catch. Now that changes things

headshotImage.caption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c MEK Hussey b Johnson 4 (3b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: he's gifted his wicket here after a superb shot the previous ball! Good length outside off, tries to swat it over the bowler's head, gets the top-edge and Hussey at cover takes a well-judged catch as it takes forever to come down

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Grant Elliott c †Haddin b Bracken 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: edged and gone! Elliot is gone first ball! Fishing for it outside off, short and wide, tried to run it down to third man, got a thin edge straight to Haddin

headshotImage.caption: Ricky Ponting player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ricky Ponting player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Neil Broom run out (Ponting) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: run out, Guptill's running out of partners here, full on the off stump, defended towards point and they attempt a quick single, Ponting runs in, picks the ball cleanly and throws down the stumps at the striker's end in one motion to find Broom well short of his ground. Could that be the decisive blow?

headshotImage.caption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills c MEK Hussey b Siddle 1 (9b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 11.11

dismissalComment.html: what a catch!! Good length on the off stump, makes room and chips it lethargically over mid-off, Michael Hussey runs back to his right, leaps and plucks it with one hand to complete a neat catch!
